FuncDef:
The undo snmp-agent get-cache disable feature-name command is used to open the get cache function of specified feature.
By default, the get cache function is enabled.

ParaDef.Info:
Feature name of set cache.
Enum value

Examples: [~HUAWEI] undo snmp-agent get-cache disable feature-name ifm
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
The SNMP get cache function improves the get performance when the NMS is used to get MIB objects. To enable the SNMP get cache function, run the undo snmp-agent get-cache disable feature-name command.
